					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records the gift of a lamp-stand and 90 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruvīraṭṭānattu-Mahādēva at Ādhirājamaṅgalyapuram by one <hi rend="bold">Veḷḷikkēaṉ Piramāli</hi> a resident of the place. The <hi rend="italic">nagarattār</hi> received the sheep and the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> agreed to maintain the lamp. This is probably an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
